### 🟡 MEDIUM — 7. No Centralized Error Handling — Stack Trace Leakage Risk (OWASP A05:2021)

**Location:** App-level (no error middleware present)

Without a custom error handler, Express's default handler may return **stack traces** to clients in development mode, or unstructured error responses in production. If routes are added that hit databases or call external services, unhandled promise rejections or thrown errors will expose internals.

**Recommendation:** Add a catch-all error handler as the **last** middleware.

```js
// ✅ Centralized error handler (must be last app.use)
