**Issue:** Express sends no security-hardening HTTP headers by default. Browsers receive no `Content-Security-Policy`, `X-Frame-Options`, `X-Content-Type-Options`, etc., leaving the app open to clickjacking, MIME-sniffing, and XSS amplification.

